🎄・OmZ 21-Sep-21 05:33 PM
Cell Wall ✓ - Found outside of the cell membrane - Nonliving layer (Just a wall, no motion) - Has passages so materials can pass through - Supports and protects the cell - Only found in plants, fungi, and bacteria Cytoplasm ✓ - Jelly-like substance enclosed by cell membrane and includes the organelles - Provides a medium for chemical reactions to take place - Cytosol = just the jelly-like substance - Contains organelles to carry out specific jobs   Nucleus ✓ - Controls the normal activities of the cell - Usually the largest organelle - Contains the DNA in chromosomes - Bounded by a nuclear envelope (membrane) with pores, DNA is too big to go through the pores, but DNA can only get out during cell division so usually it just stays inside the nucleus - Each cell has fixed number of chromosomes that carry genes - Genes control cell characteristics Nucleolus - Inside the nucleus - Disappears when cell divides - Makes ribosomes that make proteins Cytoskeleton ✓ - Helps cell maintain cell shape - Also help move organelles move around - Made of proteins - Microfilaments are threadlike and made of ACTIN - Microtubules are tube-like and made of TUBULIN Centrioles ✓ - Found only in animal cells - Paired structures near nucleus (usually parallel from each other; +) - Made of bundle of microtubules - Appear during cell division forming mitotic spindle - Help to pull chromosome pairs apart to opposite ends of the cell with the help of the mitotic spindle (edited)

cancer is in part due to cells that divide too frequently; the cells are not regulated;they are uncontrolled
10:10
Cancer cells can't communicate with other healthy cells, they may not be able to carry out normal cell functions, they may not securely anchor themselves like other cells do which can make them more likely to travel somewhere else. some cancer cells have the ability to secrete their own growth hormone, that makes blood vessels divert over to those cancer cells and supply the cancer cell with nutrients, which can take nutrients away from healthy cells.
